    "overview": "RedMart's database containing personal data of approximately 898,791 customers was exfiltrated in September 2020 after a threat actor compromised a GitHub user account and leveraged hardcoded API keys to gain unauthorised access to multiple cloud environments. The organisation failed to implement reasonable security measures including access controls, key management best practices, and database authentication, enabling a cascading breach across interconnected AWS and Alibaba cloud systems.",
