    "decision_date": "6 October 2022",
    "industry": "E-commerce / Payment processing",
    "overview": "Two Philippines-based service contractors of Shopify illegally accessed and exfiltrated customer personal data stored in Shopify's Canadian systems between June and September 2020, affecting 23,928 individuals. Both SNPL and Shopify SG breached the Transfer Limitation Obligation under section 26 of the PDPA by failing to ensure that personal data transferred outside Singapore was protected to a standard comparable to the PDPA.",
