    "overview": "On 5 December 2020, a cybersecurity breach compromised 11 systems (9 in London, 2 in Singapore) operated by Aman Group, resulting in the exfiltration of personal data of approximately 2,500 individuals. The Deputy Commissioner found that Aman Group had met its Protection obligation under section 24 of the PDPA and took no enforcement action.",
