    "case_number": "DP-2102-B7878",
    "citation": null,
    "decision_date": null,
    "industry": "Telecommunications",
    "overview": "Singapore Telecommunication Limited suffered a data breach on 10 February 2021 when threat actors exploited two zero-day vulnerabilities in a third-party File Transfer Appliance (FTA) system, exfiltrating 9,921 files containing personal data of 163,370 individuals including names, NRIC numbers, financial identifiers, addresses, contact details, photographs, identification documents, bank account and credit card information. The Deputy Commissioner found that the organisation had implemented reasonable security measures and could not have detected or prevented the incident as it had no control or visibility over the zero-day vulnerabilities in the vendor's proprietary system, resulting in no enforcement action.",
