    "root_cause": "Belden Singapore failed to execute a legally binding Deed of Accession to the Global Data Transfer Agreement (GDTA) before transferring personal data overseas, meaning contractual protections were not enforceable despite operational safeguards being in place.",
    "outcome": "Belden Singapore was administered a warning for breach of the Transfer Limitation Obligation under section 26 of the PDPA. No financial penalty was imposed. GVSPL was found to be in compliance. Belden Singapore subsequently remedied the lapse by signing a Deed of Accession on 18 June 2021.",
    "penalty": null,
    "mitigating": [
      "Breach was technical and procedural rather than substantive",
      "All operational policies, practices and technical measures were implemented to provide comparable protection",
      "Lapse was rectified by signing Deed of Accession post-incident",
      "Overseas transferee was related group company with full implementation of data protection standards"
    ],
    "aggravating": [],
    "_id": "breach-of-the-transfer-limitation-obligation-by-belden-singapore"
