    "overview": "J & R Bossini Fashion Pte Ltd suffered a ransomware attack on 27 May 2020 that encrypted customer data of 154,213 Singapore customers and employee data of 120 employees, with at least 14,082 customer records exfiltrated. The organisation breached its obligations under the PDPA by transferring customer data to Hong Kong without legally enforceable protections and failing to implement group-level policies documenting data protection responsibilities, creating uncertainty about security accountability.",
