    "overview": "An applicant requested access to HSBC's internal evaluation report for his unsuccessful credit card application, but HSBC redacted opinion data generated by its proprietary algorithm. The Deputy Commissioner confirmed HSBC's refusal to disclose the redacted data, establishing that the Evaluative Purpose Exception under the Fifth Schedule of the PDPA applies to opinion data kept solely for evaluating suitability for credit products.",
