    "decision_date": "18 June 2020",
    "industry": "Information Technology Services / Software Development",
    "overview": "Times Software failed to protect employee personal data of three client organisations (Dentons, Red Hat, Liberty Specialty Markets) which was exposed online after a hard disk failure in December 2017. The data remained accessible via Google search from December 2017 to February 2018, affecting 616 employees. The incident exposed sensitive information including names, NRICs, residential addresses, salaries, and bank account details.",
