    "overview": "MDIS Corporation failed to implement adequate security measures for personal data collected through an online course registration form, resulting in a Microsoft Excel spreadsheet containing information on 304 individuals being publicly accessible via Google search. The organisation did not communicate data protection requirements to its vendor and developer, nor conduct adequate security testing before launch, leaving the data exposed to unauthorised access for approximately 6 months.",
