    "root_cause": "MCST 3593 failed to put in place written data protection clauses in its contract with the security services provider, implement data protection policies, appoint a Data Protection Officer, or communicate data protection requirements to service providers. New-E lacked written policies and training on data protection, relying instead on verbal instructions which were not adhered to by staff.",
    "outcome": "MCST 3593 directed to pay financial penalty of $5,000 within 30 days. New-E directed to implement data protection policy and internal guidelines including procedures for CCTV footage management and access control within 30 days and report completion to the Commission within 7 days. ETCPM found not in breach.",
