    "case_number": "DP-1801-B1530",
    "citation": "[2019] SGPDPC 20",
    "decision_date": "20 June 2019",
    "industry": "Insurance",
    "overview": "AIA Singapore's letter generation system contained a logic error that caused 245 letters containing sensitive insurance data to be sent to two customers with incorrect local despatch addresses due to a faulty software fix. The organisation failed to conduct adequate testing of the fix and lacked controls to verify the accuracy of automatically generated correspondence containing sensitive personal data.",
