    "overview": "IES's website suffered a data breach in September 2014 when user IDs, passwords, and member personal data were posted on Pastebin. The Commission found that IES failed to implement reasonable security arrangements required under section 24 of the PDPA, allowing over 6,000 member credentials and 60,000+ phone numbers to be exposed.",
